This paper proposes a method for automatically estimating grass biomass from roadside image data using artificial neural networks and Gabor wavelet filter vote. The paper heavily relies on computer vision techniques such as image processing, feature extraction, and classification. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as feedforward artificial neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques such as feature extraction and classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves geographic information systems (GIS) and fire-prone region identification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GR (Graphics).
